  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Core responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan, organize and control Design operations to ensure efficient delegation of duties and responsibilities</li><li>Review project specifications, technical clarifications and construction drawings</li><li>Assist in tender preparations & technical submissions</li><li>Liaise with client’s representatives, consultants and subcontractors on technical matters</li><li>Prepare drawings for Authorities submission and approval</li><li>Provide advices to the project staffs for the details on the operation process and the material wastages control</li><li>Ensure designed quality of works is achieved and regulatory requirement are complied with</li><li>Able to forward details costing on installation as request</li></ul><p><strong>Job Specification</strong></p><p><strong>Minimum Educational Qualifications/ Experience required:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree / Diploma Civil or/& Structural Engineering or its equivalent</li><li>Minimum 3 years' relevant metal works design experience</li><li>Experienced in Structural design and calculation for building projects</li><li>Experienced in coordination with clients, consultants for building projects</li><li>Fresh University Graduates are welcome to apply </li><li>No experience are welcome to consider Asst Technical Engineer </li></ul><p><strong>Special requirements: </strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge of Structural Design Codes (UBC / IBC / SNI) is essential</li><li>Able to work under stress and tight schedule</li><li>Able to propose VE items if necessary</li><li>Well-versed in MS Office and the latest version of AutoCad</li></ul>",
